Now, here‚Äôs where the anomalies come in. None of the Western Field guns frames were case hardened, this one was. The serial numbers are not even in the Western Field range. The Western Field guns stocks were not checkered and were not normally good Walnut, the stocks on this gun are checkered and have a bit of natural tiger striping in the walnut.

This is a VERY unusual gun. It‚Äôs in an unadulterated form and in perfect functioning condition.

The bores are pristine. Both of the sighting beads have been broken. Bluing on the barrels is excellent with a very few minor surface scratches. The Duck in the Swamp scenes are light, but distinguishable. They aren‚Äôt worn, just lightly stamped. The frame is dark, but there is no indication that it has been blued.

The barrels are 12 Ga., 30‚Äù choked full and modified.

title: For Sale:  Walnut USGI M14, M1A stock with handguard.  Cartouche marks.
postcontent:
USGI issue M14 walnut stock for sale.  It will fit an M1A (I actually dry fit it fine on mine).  It is Vietnam war era with handle and side cartouche marks.  The stock has all the metal including front ferrule, front swivel, plates inside action and full rear folding plate.  Also comes with aluminum brown hand guard.
This was a service stock with service wear.  As such there are some dents dings and scratches that you would expect.  There are two "fingernail" scratches on the stock that could be sanded out on the forearm, but there are no cracks in the stock.  This is a perfect candidate for refinishing if you so chose.  Work I have done includes removing butt plate then steaming it to remove cosmoline.  It was then wiped down with mineral spirits and washed it with Murphy's oil soap. Lastly the stock was hand rubbed with 100% Tung oil and the butt plate was wiped with Rem-oil and re-installed. I did not remove the tape where the armorer had indicated windage and elevation for the rifle when in service.  I feel strongly that I did not want to sand or strip all the layers of age,oil and dents off the stock as they give it character and are actual signs of it's history.  If fully stripped and sanded the stock would be much lighter in color.

Price is $85 and I can meet FTF in the Triad.  I will ship anywhere in the US for $100.  Prefer Paypal.  No trades.

Email through Armslist and I will respond.  Thanks.

title: For Sale:  NEW Beretta PX4 Storm 9mm Full Size Handgun -firearm, gun
postcontent:
*Take 3% off the price for cash, money order, or certified check payments*

Beretta PX4 Storm Full Size

Low barrel axis position

Thanks to the design of the direct barrel-slide locking system, the low barrel axis reduces felt recoil and minimizes muzzle rise.

Newly designed slide

The sides of the slide are smooth and offer snag-proof insertion and removal of the pistol from its holster. The front and rear serrations on the slide facilitate slide operation and safety control in moist conditions.

3-Dot Sight System

Features a white '3-dot' sight pattern for quick acquisition of the target. The rear sight is designed to provide a front projection so that, in an emergency, the user may retract the slide single-handedly by pushing the rear sight against the edge of a table, door, etc.

Simple Field Stripping

Pistol is designed for extremely quick and simple field stripping. Disassembly latch does not remove from the gun, preventing accidental dropping and loss. Reassembly is easy and accidental misassembly of parts is prevented by the distinctive design.

External Hammer Design

A traditional feature of Beretta pistols, this design provides the most energy to the firing pin, virtually eliminating the possibility of misfires due to light primer strikes. Also provides an immediate visual and tactile indicator as to the cocked/uncocked status of the pistol.

Ambidextrous Safety (Type F)

The ambidextrous safety lever, easily accessible by the thumb or a right or left handed shooter, is spring loaded so it's either positively "on" or "off". The safety lever also functions as the pistol's decocking lever. When pushed down, the rear part of the firing pin (striker) is rotated out of alignment with the front part of the firing pin. (NOTE: Type C does not have an external safety/decocking lever.) Additional hammer drop catch (half cock notch) prevents striking of the firing pin unit in the remote chance of unintentional hammer drop

Visible Automatic Firing Pin Block

The front part of the firing pin is blocked from any forward movement until the trigger is pulled completely back. The block is located rearward, far away from the fouling and debris of the breech face. Since the bloack is visible, the user may ascertain its proper operation at any time. Even if the pistol falls and strikes the ground muzzle down, the firing pin will not strike the primer

No Glare Finish

Beretta's exclusive BrunitonTM non-reflective black coating is a superior corrosion and wear resistant finish

Slide

The sides of the slide are smooth and offer snag-proof insertion and removal of the pistol from its holster. The front and rear serrations on the slide facilitate slide operation and safety control in both wet or dry conditions

Accessory Rail

The frame of the Px4 Storm has an integral Picatinny MIL-STD-1913 rail for rapic attachment of tacitcal lights and laser aiming devices

Reversible Magazine Release

Multiple-sized, reversible magazine release buttons allow for customization to the individual's hand size. Small size comes standard on the gun, while medium and large buttons are available as accessories and easy replacement. Each size may be positioned for right-handed or left-handed use

Individual Size Grips

Pistol may be configured with small, medium or large back-straps to individually fit the hand of each shooter. The backstraps are checkered to ensure a firm grip in both wet or dry shooting conditions. Three backstraps included with every pistol.

Magazine

High capacity steel magazines are durable and drop-free, even when empty, when the magazine button is depressed. Standard flush magazines may be complemented with optional extended magazines that increase the capacity by 3 rounds (1 round for .45 Auto caliber).
